;; Standard Clojure Style config — https://github.com/oakmac/standard-clojure-style-js
;;
;; This project's source is mostly let-go (.lg), which is Clojure-syntax. NOTE:
;; standard-clj only recognizes .lg via the `--file-ext lg` CLI flag — there is
;; no .edn key to register a file extension — so run it as `make fmt-check` /
;; `make fmt` (which pass the flag), or `standard-clj fix --file-ext lg .`.
;; A bare `standard-clj` (no flag) only sees .clj/.cljs/.cljc.
;;
;; The check-on-edit Claude Code hook (tools/standard_clj_check_hook.py) passes
;; the flag too, so edits to .lg files are checked as Clojure.
{:ignore ["**/node_modules/**"
          "dist/**"
          "tests/e2e/test-results/**"]}
